==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sweal
<hw>Sweal</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Swealed</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Swealing</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[OE. <ets>swelen</ets> to burn,
AS. <ets>swelan</ets>; akin to G. <ets>schwelen</ets> to burn slowly,
<ets>schw⟦uum⟧l</ets> sultry, Icel. <ets>svaela</ets> a thick
smoke.]</ety> <def>To melt and run down, as the tallow of a candle; to
waste away without feeding the flame.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>swale</asp>.]</altsp> <rj><au>Sir W. Scott.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sweal</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Sweal
<hw>Sweal</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To singe; to scorch; to swale;
<as>as, to <ex>sweal</ex> a pig by singeing off the hair</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Swear</ent>⟦br⟧
